snippet.textDisplay:
This years quarter finalists is superb Nearly every player has a chance of getting to the final

Aspinal has been superb this year,he takes his chances
Van den bergh was poor against Lewis (compared to his other games)and still came back from 3-1 down

Wright-imo this guy is due a major trophy. He is superb. But he survived a scare today.

Durrant is a great player easily top 10 in the world and since he has joined the pdc he has been in 2 major semi finals also he has won the bdo. He has experience of winning world titles

Luke Humphries is an amazing player he needs to play with the same intensity and he is on the side of the bracket with no MVG He is being sleepen on

Gerwyn price in my opinion can go all the way and win the tournament after his grand slam heroics(this year) but it depends on which one of gerwyn price shows up. If it’s the grand slam gerwyn price or the price who played against Whitlock On his day price is one of the best in darts

Of course MVG is MVG but if he beat labanauskas he plays either van den bergh or aspinall. What a match we could have on our hands

Final - MVG VS WRIGHT

MVG for the win but I hope Wright can do it
